author: @FollowingTheDream455
text: This is a pretty cool idea! I made a project  where I'd used spoons to create sunflowers a couple of years ago. I took 6 or 7 white plastic spoons, and painted them mostly yellow, with a small light orange line down the middle. I criss crossed all the spoons in a cricular pattern and hot glued them together. Then, I cut out a circle from a paper plate and hot glued various sizes and colors of wood beads in the center. I placed the circle with the wooden beads in the center of the spoon circle and hot glued the circle to multiple spoons in a circular pattern. I then took a dark brown wicker basket and weaved twine through the wicker basket and around the necks of the spoons. The circular shape of the wicker basket allowed me to easily hang my sunflower and wicker basket decoration, using something as simple as a thumb tack.
